The paper proposes a framework for enhancing various types of neural networks with declarative first-order logic rules, which is relevant to several sub-fields of computer science. The use of logic rules suggests a focus on artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and natural language processing (cs.CL), while the application of the framework to CNNs and RNNs suggests a focus on machine learning (cs.LG) and neural networks (cs.NE). The deployment of the framework on a CNN for sentiment analysis and an RNN for named entity recognition suggests a focus on computer vision (cs.CV) and natural language processing (cs.CL) respectively.
